20:32.232 --> 20:34.732
<i>Is it over there?</i>

20:34.734 --> 20:35.933
( camera snaps )

20:38.270 --> 20:41.405
I'd say it's getting
pretty crazy, don't you think?

20:41.407 --> 20:42.974
Who's that?
She looks familiar.

20:42.976 --> 20:44.809
Are you in my office?
What?

20:44.811 --> 20:47.345
<i>Look around.</i>
<i>( sighs )</i>

20:56.388 --> 20:58.256
Aaaaah!

20:58.258 --> 20:59.790
<i>Amanda!</i>

21:01.893 --> 21:03.261
<i>Amanda.</i>

21:04.263 --> 21:05.263
Amanda?

21:05.265 --> 21:06.998
Who is this?

21:07.000 --> 21:09.500
It's <i>me,</i> amanda!
Now focus! The tonic!

21:09.502 --> 21:13.371
No, you're not.
That is impossible.

21:13.373 --> 21:14.939
You have worked
for me for 15 years.

21:14.941 --> 21:16.307
<i>We have mounted</i>

21:16.309 --> 21:17.441
22 productions together,
and turned

21:17.443 --> 21:19.310
<i>Three unknowns</i>
<i>into broadway stars.</i>

21:19.312 --> 21:23.014
And help me figure out
what is in this tonic
that turned me young,

21:23.016 --> 21:25.816
I will fire you
without hesitation or regret!

21:25.818 --> 21:26.984
Now pull yourself together!

21:26.986 --> 21:31.289
Oh, my god. It <i>is</i> you.

21:31.291 --> 21:34.025
Thank you.
What have you got?

21:34.027 --> 21:35.693
<i>Um...</i>

21:35.695 --> 21:39.063
Oh, god. The stuff
is really old, harper.

21:39.065 --> 21:40.998
It was used for

21:41.000 --> 21:43.301
<i>Rheumatism, gout, um...</i>

21:43.303 --> 21:45.936
Melancholia, and impotence.

21:45.938 --> 21:47.538
What about side effects?

21:47.540 --> 21:49.473
Well, I've already
looked online.

21:49.475 --> 21:51.776
The company's been
out of business
for decades.

21:57.683 --> 22:02.653
Find out: Does it wear off,
and if so, can I take more.
You got it? Find out.

22:19.971 --> 22:21.539
( exhales )

22:21.541 --> 22:24.342
The things I do
for my daughter.

22:29.614 --> 22:31.115
Hi.

22:31.117 --> 22:32.516
Hello.

22:32.518 --> 22:33.884
Debbie hayworth.

22:33.886 --> 22:35.386
Marco vitturi.

22:35.388 --> 22:38.789
You must be related to
mirabella. You look like her.

22:38.791 --> 22:41.859
She looks like me.
We're second cousins.

22:41.861 --> 22:44.095
Once removed.
Aunt marjorie's side.

22:44.097 --> 22:45.730
Right. Listen to this.

22:45.732 --> 22:47.498
"dear mirabella,

22:47.500 --> 22:49.600
"you are so beautiful.

22:49.602 --> 22:53.104
"I want to never sleep
or even blink again

22:53.106 --> 22:57.742
"just so I can stare at
your beautifulness forever...

22:57.744 --> 22:59.977
Until I die."

22:59.979 --> 23:02.480
Too over the top?

23:02.482 --> 23:06.050
Wow. That is, um...
Yeah, that's really bad.

23:06.052 --> 23:08.919
It's terrible.

23:08.921 --> 23:12.123
But it was mirabella's idea
for us to write our own vows
for the wedding,

23:12.125 --> 23:14.125
And...I don't know,

23:14.127 --> 23:16.794
I have no idea
what I'm gonna say.

23:16.796 --> 23:19.630
Looks to me like
you can't <i>stop</i> figuring out
what to say.

23:19.632 --> 23:21.031
True enough.

23:21.033 --> 23:24.902
Love can make you
a little crazy sometimes.

23:24.904 --> 23:27.405
That's not your reputation,
you know.

23:27.407 --> 23:29.140
Yeah. I know.

23:29.142 --> 23:32.076
Must be really hard
to give that up.

23:32.078 --> 23:35.413
Not really.

23:35.415 --> 23:39.116
Mirabella must be
very special to you.
Oh, she is.

23:39.118 --> 23:41.118
She has this--

23:41.120 --> 23:43.521
I mean, she's so--

23:43.523 --> 23:47.458
When we first met,
I was like--

23:47.460 --> 23:50.127
Oh, god.

23:50.129 --> 23:52.062
She's--everything.

23:52.064 --> 23:55.199
So it's kind of hard,
you know, to--

23:56.735 --> 23:59.770
She has <i>the</i> most
beautiful blue eyes.

23:59.772 --> 24:02.473
Yeah. Yeah,
she got those
from her dad.

24:02.475 --> 24:07.044
And this beautiful smile
where one side of her mouth
kind of turns up--

24:07.046 --> 24:10.147
Kind of like yours.
Think she's got a secret?

24:10.149 --> 24:14.852
Yeah, right.
Something, uh...Secret.

24:14.854 --> 24:18.489
Oh, and she--she has
these beautiful hands.

24:18.491 --> 24:20.925
Oh, dancer's hands.

24:20.927 --> 24:24.061
You're...A dancer too?

24:24.063 --> 24:26.030
Runs in the family.

24:28.500 --> 24:32.703
I'm--I'm sorry, have--
have we met before?

24:32.705 --> 24:35.773
Not in this lifetime.

24:35.775 --> 24:38.576
Are you sure? Because--
oh, I'm sure.

24:38.578 --> 24:41.979
You would definitely
remember meeting me.

24:41.981 --> 24:45.683
You know, for second cousins,
you and mirabella...

24:45.685 --> 24:49.086
Yes?
It's strange how much
you remind me of her.

24:56.962 --> 24:59.864
This is so going to work.

25:05.070 --> 25:07.071
Noelle, how many times
did you lose your virginity?

25:07.073 --> 25:09.773
I have no idea, but hey,

25:09.775 --> 25:13.143
If the stars align
I might lose it again
this weekend.

25:13.145 --> 25:15.513
( laughter )

25:15.515 --> 25:18.682
Seriously though, em,
you're so lucky to have
found a guy like marco.

25:18.684 --> 25:21.852
He's so hot and rich...

25:21.854 --> 25:25.756
And hot and rich! Hello!

25:25.758 --> 25:27.057
Okay, mirabella,
it's your turn.

25:27.059 --> 25:29.226
Oh, no.
Somebody else go.

25:29.228 --> 25:31.161
But your story's so good.

25:31.163 --> 25:33.531
Okay. She was 16 years old,

25:33.533 --> 25:36.000
She told her mom
she was spending the weekend
at a friend's house--

25:36.002 --> 25:37.735
I'm that friend,
that influence--
and instead,

25:37.737 --> 25:41.105
We snuck off to paris!
What?!

25:41.107 --> 25:44.141
I mean, wow.

25:44.143 --> 25:47.144
And there,
after staying up all night

25:47.146 --> 25:48.979
Walking the banks of the seine
hand in hand,

25:48.981 --> 25:51.282
Talking until sunrise,

25:51.284 --> 25:53.150
Whispering their life stories
to each other--

25:53.152 --> 25:55.953
Noelle, no!
You have got
to be kidding me.

25:55.955 --> 25:58.989
Our dear, sweet,
innocent mirabella

25:58.991 --> 26:03.327
Laid herself down
with that hot, sexy
french man

26:03.329 --> 26:07.064
And gave up
her precious flower.
At sixteen?!

26:07.066 --> 26:08.966
It was very romantic.

26:08.968 --> 26:11.635
By the end of the night
we knew everything
about each other

26:11.637 --> 26:13.904
And we were like
two ships passing.

26:13.906 --> 26:16.307
And he was really very sweet.
Wait a second.

26:16.309 --> 26:20.044
How the heck did you
get out of the country
without your mother knowing?

26:20.046 --> 26:22.179
Her mom was at
an out-of-town preview.

26:22.181 --> 26:24.648
Her dad gave us permission.
We told him it was
a class trip.

26:24.650 --> 26:26.584
My mom didn't even
notice I was gone.

26:26.586 --> 26:29.587
Okay, that is not fair.
She's a very busy woman.

26:29.589 --> 26:31.755
A single mom,
a demanding career--

26:31.757 --> 26:34.992
Debbie, my mom is, was,
and always will be

26:34.994 --> 26:37.928
Way too self-centered
to think about anybody
but herself.

26:37.930 --> 26:41.932
She took you to dance classes
three times a week
when you were a kid.

26:48.740 --> 26:50.341
