32:29.580 --> 32:32.950
But now this?

32:32.952 --> 32:36.987
I don't think I can be
the man she wants me to be,

32:36.989 --> 32:39.156
Or the man she deserves.

32:41.626 --> 32:43.961
I'm not good enough
for her. Right?

32:46.130 --> 32:49.633
I'm sorry, debbie,
this isn't your fault.
It's mine.

32:49.635 --> 32:51.702
I have to go.

33:14.325 --> 33:16.693
Oh! This is it.

33:16.695 --> 33:20.464
Can you believe
I'm getting married tomorrow?

33:20.466 --> 33:22.733
No, I really can't.

33:25.103 --> 33:27.137
Debbie, what's wrong?

33:27.139 --> 33:29.039
Nothing. Nothing.

33:29.041 --> 33:32.075
I'm fine, it's just
this is the first time
I've seen you in your dress.

33:32.077 --> 33:36.213
It seems like just yesterday
you were a little girl.

33:36.215 --> 33:39.149
We. <i>We</i> were little girls.

33:39.151 --> 33:41.084
Dancing around
the back yard together,

33:41.086 --> 33:43.687
Playing with
each other's hair...

33:45.490 --> 33:49.459
This is the most
beautiful you've looked
in your entire life.

33:49.461 --> 33:51.228
Are you happy?

33:51.230 --> 33:53.263
Yes!

33:53.265 --> 33:55.232
How could I not be?

33:55.234 --> 33:58.068
I'm getting everything
that I ever wanted.

33:58.070 --> 34:03.206
But you're giving up
your dream to be a dancer
to stay here with marco.

34:03.208 --> 34:06.576
( laughs )
debbie.

34:06.578 --> 34:11.181
Can I...
Can I tell you a secret?

34:11.183 --> 34:14.184
I never wanted
to be a dancer.

34:14.186 --> 34:19.188
That was my mom's dream,
not mine.

34:20.123 --> 34:24.194
What? Never?

34:24.196 --> 34:28.632
I mean, maybe for
a little while,
when I was a kid.

34:28.634 --> 34:32.369
I mean,
I worshipped my mother.

34:32.371 --> 34:35.237
You remember, she was
this big glamorous star

34:35.239 --> 34:37.340
And everyone loved her.

34:37.342 --> 34:40.342
And I wanted to be
just like her...

34:40.344 --> 34:43.313
For a while.

34:43.315 --> 34:45.081
What happened?

34:45.083 --> 34:48.284
I grew up.

34:50.188 --> 34:54.524
I can't believe
you never said anything
to your mom.

34:54.525 --> 34:57.094
Well...

34:57.096 --> 35:00.130
I didn't want
to disappoint her.

35:00.132 --> 35:02.599
When my mom blew her knee out,

35:02.601 --> 35:05.268
She wanted me
to be the big star that...

35:05.270 --> 35:07.804
She couldn't be anymore.

35:07.806 --> 35:10.774
And when I met marco,

35:10.776 --> 35:16.313
I finally realized
I can't live my life for her,

35:16.315 --> 35:19.416
No matter how much I love her.

35:23.154 --> 35:25.288
It was like...

35:25.290 --> 35:27.524
The first time
marco and I met,

35:27.526 --> 35:29.759
I could hear this little voice
telling me,

35:29.761 --> 35:33.163
"this guy's the one."

35:33.165 --> 35:34.631
Ya know? Like...

35:34.633 --> 35:37.234
The future was talking to me,

35:37.236 --> 35:41.171
Telling me I had already
spent a whole lifetime with him.

35:41.173 --> 35:44.474
Does that sound crazy?

35:44.476 --> 35:47.210
No.

35:47.212 --> 35:50.881
It's the most romantic
thing I've ever heard.

35:50.883 --> 35:53.183
Woman:
Senorina mirabella?

35:55.220 --> 36:00.790
Oh. You know, I forgot
to thank you for standing in
for noelle today, debbie.

36:00.792 --> 36:02.359
I--

36:04.262 --> 36:07.297
I have no idea where
she could possibly be.

36:09.200 --> 36:11.201
Debbie, where are you going?

36:11.203 --> 36:13.470
See you at
the rehearsal dinner!

